    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-20T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-20T20:00:00-05:00" n="271"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d271">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9549: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-21T10:00:00+09:00"
                            >August 21, 1937—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 21—9:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>290. 1. An official of the Foreign Office called under instructions this morning
                    at the Embassy to express regret over the casualties <pb facs="0279" n="271"
                        xml:id="pg_271"/> incurred by members of the crew of the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Augusta</hi> now at Shanghai. The official stated that the Foreign Office
                    had received no official report from Shanghai but that according to press
                    reports the casualties were caused by a shell fired by the Chinese: that the
                    Foreign Office is mindful, however, that the incident would not have arisen had
                    there been no hostilities between the Japanese and Chinese forces: and that the
                    Foreign Office desires to express its sincere regrets for the loss of life and
                    the injury incurred by members of the American Navy.</p>
                <p>2. We informed the official that we appreciate the action of the Foreign Office
                    in instructing the official to call, and that the Department would be duly
                    informed.</p>
                <p>3. Repeated to Shanghai for relay to Nanking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
